You gain a new {g|Encyclopedia:Special_Abilities}spell-like ability{/g}, each usable twice per day, from the following list, in order:
1. {g|SpellsVanish}vanish{/g}
2. {g|SpellsSleep}sleep{/g}
3. {g|SpellsBlur}blur{/g}
4. {g|SpellsInvisibility}invisibility{/g}
5. {g|SpellsDeepSlumber}deep slumber{/g}
6. {g|SpellsDisplacement}displacement{/g}
7. {g|SpellsConfusion}confusion{/g}
8. {g|SpellsDominatePerson}dominate person{/g}.
For example, the first time you select this {g|Encyclopedia:Feat}feat{/g}, you gain vanish 2/day; the second time you select this feat, you gain sleep 2/day. Your {g|Encyclopedia:Caster_Level}caster level{/g} for these {g|Encyclopedia:Spell}spells{/g} is equal to your {g|Encyclopedia:Hit_Dice}Hit Dice{/g}. The {g|Encyclopedia:DC}DCs{/g} for these abilities are {g|Encyclopedia:Charisma}Charisma{/g}-based.
You may select this feat up to eight times. Each time you take it, you gain an additional ability as described above.
